definition: to submit (a report etc)/to refer (a problem) to sb
to carry (hanging down from the hand)/to lift/to put forward/to mention/to raise (an issue)/upwards character stroke/lifting brush stroke (in painting)/scoop for measuring liquid
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: Material evidence must also be original.
How do I submit an expense report?

sentences.chinese: 對於生物製品，應當要提交連續幾個生產批次的樣品。

sentences.english: Candidates may be required to produce medical proof of their disability.
sentences.chinese: 申請人或須提交醫生證明書，以證明他爲殘疾人士。

sentences.english: The results of the BCA consumer research project also will be presented.
sentences.chinese: 結果基本能力評估的消費者研究項目也將提交。

sentences.english: Indicate by a check mark whether the registrant has filed all reports required.

sentences.english: The bill, which has 31 co-sponsors, has been forwarded to the House Ways and Means Committee for consideration.

sentences.english: The proxy service monitors the status of each job that has been submitted.

sentences.english: The stub and skeleton objects also take care of beginning and committing container-managed transactions.

sentences.chinese: 可是州外的收集者卻要提交特許證或警察發給的證書。

sentences.english: Proofs submitted by the printer should be carefully checked to eliminate typographical errors.
sentences.chinese: 排版工人應當仔細覈對提交的校樣，避免印刷錯誤。
